## Tool registry (`src/lib/ai/tools/`)

```
src/lib/ai/tools/
├── tool-registry.ts         Flat array of AIToolDefinitions
├── tool-registry.types.ts   defineTool helper, types
├── tool-result.types.ts     Discriminated result types
├── tool-proposal.types.ts   Proposal shapes per tool
├── tool-executor.ts         Shared execution wrapper (logging, errors)
├── ai-sdk-adapter.ts        Converts AIToolDefinitions → Vercel AI SDK tools
├── pagination.ts            Shared list-truncation logic
├── sanitize.ts              Strip unsafe content from tool args/results
└── definitions/
    ├── <tool>.schema.ts     Zod parameter schema
    ├── <tool>.handler.ts    execute() implementation
    └── index.ts             Barrel export
```

### Adding a tool (read-only, `get_*`)

1. Add `<name>.schema.ts` exporting a `z.object({...})` parameter schema.
2. Add `<name>.handler.ts` exporting `async function execute<Name>(params, ctx)`.
   - `ctx: ToolExecutionContext` has `orgId`, `locationId`, `clerkUserId`,
     `role`, `conversationId`, `timezone`.
   - Return a **discriminated result** from `tool-result.types.ts` (e.g.
     `{ type: "success", data, uiHint }` or `{ type: "error", message }`).
3. Barrel-export both from `definitions/index.ts`.
4. Register in `tool-registry.ts` via `defineTool({ name, description,
   requiredPermission, parameters, execute })`.
5. `requiredPermission` must be an `AIPermission` from
   `lib/ai/rbac/permissions.ts`. Pick the most restrictive that still
   makes the tool useful.

### Adding a mutation tool (`propose_*`)

- Do **all** of the above, but `execute` must create a `StoredProposal`
  and never mutate. See `propose-shift-swap.handler.ts` for the canonical
  reference (OCC token, dry-run, proposal summary).
- Add the matching execution branch to
  `lib/ai/orchestrator/execute-proposal.ts` so the confirm endpoint knows
  how to materialize the proposal into a real service call.

---

## RBAC (`src/lib/ai/rbac/`)

- `permissions.ts` defines `AIPermission` and `ROLE_PERMISSIONS` (frozen).
  Each `MemberRole` maps to an allow-list of permissions.
- `filter-tools.ts` narrows the full tool registry to the subset the
  current user may call, based on their role.
- RBAC is enforced in **two places** — the filter (so the LLM can't even
  see tools it can't call) **and** the proposal resolve endpoint (so a
  stale proposal can't be executed after a role change).
- Never remove a tool from the registry and expect RBAC to catch it
  downstream — both layers must agree.

---

## Orchestrator context (`src/lib/ai/orchestrator/`)

- `build-context.ts` produces an `OrchestratorContext` for every chat
  turn: authenticated user, tenant, role, allowed tools, and verified
  viewport context (the page the user is on).
- `viewport` is validated with `@sous/types` `viewportContextSchema` and
  **verified** via `verify-viewport-access.ts` — you can't claim to be
  looking at a schedule you don't have access to.
- `system-prompt.ts` builds the final system prompt: restaurant
  identity, role-specific guidance, viewport context, date/time in the
  location's timezone, and the rules of the propose/confirm protocol.

